title: FDBarGuage
body:
## Project URL
https://github.com/fulldecent/FDBarGauge

## Category
Form

## Description
This control is intended to replicate/simulate the level indicator on an audio mixing board. These indicators are usually segmented/stacked LEDs, with several colors to indicate thresholds. This control replicates that look, using Quartz drawing primitives, and auto-adjusts to horizontal or vertical orientation. Additionally, the colors, number of bars, peak hold, and other items are easily customized. Intended uses include:



## Why it should be included to `awesome-ios` (mandatory)
It's simple and people like to visually show numbers.

title: Add A-StyleInjection
body:
<!--- Provide a general summary of your changes in the Title above -->

## Project URL
https://github.com/Animaxx/A-StyleInjection

## Category
UI

## Description
A Style Injection provides the injection way to customize the whole iOS App base on the single configuration file without extra coding.

## Why it should be included to `awesome-ios` (mandatory)

In iOS projects, style always one of the important aspects. 
We might need to change the style at the mid or the end of the development. Not like Web application that we can update the CSS file to completely change the style of the App, change the whole project style could be difficulty. 
Style Injection provides the way to do it by only add a config file without coding, also, there is not much similar project like this.
